cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with detecting anomalies in Internet Protocol networks. It could also belong to "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) as network anomaly detection is an important aspect of network security. The use of statistical tests and machine learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of matrix decomposition techniques suggests that it could also belong to "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
